# Brewlab Feature Architecture

- Follow strict flow: `View -> Controller -> UseCase -> Repository -> DataSource`.
- Organize by feature under `lib/features/<feature_name>/`.
- Keep responsive view dispatcher in `<feature>_view.dart` and actual UIs in `presentation/`.
- Keep business request/response in `usecases/`; keep API/DB access only in data sources.
- Keep route names in `core/navigation/app_route_names.dart` and routes in `core/navigation/router_provider.dart`.
- Register every new data source, repository, and use case in `lib/di.dart`.
- Match existing JSON contract style: request body usually under `"Body" -> "Request"`.
- Do not introduce new architecture patterns unless explicitly requested by user.

# Implementation Style

- Mirror nearby feature naming and file patterns before inventing abstractions.
- Keep edits minimal and local; avoid cross-feature refactors unless user asks.
- Surface API failures through existing failure flow (`FailureBus`) used in this codebase.
